title: Seeks Concern For Homosexuals
creator: Morgan S
description: Written before Grinnell College had an established student organization or any formal support for the LGBTQIA+ community, this letter to the editor expresses an anonymous student's concerns for the place of homosexuals at the College. It describes the isolation that many gay students at Grinnell College felt before the formation of the Grinnell College Gay Community and the establishment of the Stonewall Resource Center. The writer is issuing a call to action to create some kind of gay community at the College, which was soon answered by the formation of GCGC.
subject: Gay Rights, Gay Community, Closeted LGBTQ+ People, Gay Movement
source: Grinnell College Scarlet and Black Student Newspaper
